snippet: Ayatollah Ali Khamenei said he supported diplomatic efforts during the president’s trip to the United Nations but said that “some of the events” had been “inappropriate.”
abstract: Iran’s supreme leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei expresses support for Pres Hassan Rouhani's outreach to West but criticizes some actions as inappropriate; may have been referring to phone call during which Rouhani and Pres Obama agreed to accelerate talks aimed at defusing dispute over Iran’s nuclear program.

byline.contributor: Jackie Calmes contributed reporting from Washington.

lead_paragraph: Ayatollah Ali Khamenei said he supported diplomatic efforts during the president’s trip to the United Nations but said that “some of the events” had been “inappropriate.”

headline.main: From Iranian Ayatollah, Support for U.S. Outreach, but Also Criticism
headline.print_headline: From Iranian Ayatollah, Support for U.S. Outreach, but Also Criticism
